      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems with analytical solutions (beam bending, contact patch) were solved and results matched to within 1% prior to study simulations. Code verification activities documented in each team's V&V plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence studies performed by all three teams using h-refinement. Peak von Mises stress and construct stiffness changed by less than 2% on final mesh relative to next coarser level, confirming discretization error is negligible relative to experimental scatter."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver residuals monitored and converged to 1e-6 for all load steps. Direct solver cross-checks performed on representative models confirmed identical results within machine precision."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Simulation inputs reviewed by a second analyst at each of the three modeling teams. Boundary condition application and material assignment scripts version-controlled and peer-reviewed prior to execution."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium alloy constitutive model justified by strain gauge measurements confirming predominantly elastic response at test loads. Contact formulation (penalty-based, frictionless at screw-rod interface) validated against prior literature. Model form uncertainty bounded by ensemble spread across three independent modeling teams."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from certified coupon test data for Ti-6Al-4V ELI per ASTM F136. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of actual test specimens with tolerances documented. Torque values for screw-rod interface applied per manufacturer specification and confirmed by calibrated torque wrench records."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested, exceeding minimum sample size for statistical characterization. Constructs sourced from a single production lot; dimensional inspection confirmed geometric variability within specification. Sample provenance documented by chain of custody records."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level. NOTE: This factor does not meet the required level — a single compressive load condition was tested; multi-angle and cyclic conditions were not included.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted per ASTM F1717 at a single compression-bending angle (5 degrees) at two independent laboratories. Environmental conditions (ambient temperature, humidity) controlled and recorded. Laboratory-to-laboratory reproducibility confirmed. However, only one load condition was evaluated, limiting coverage of the operational loading space and resulting in an achieved level below the required threshold."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Simulation input parameters mapped one-to-one to experimental measurements. Material properties, geometry, boundary conditions, and applied loads in each model directly traceable to corresponding experimental records. Traceability matrix documented and reviewed by all three modeling teams."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness (primary QoI) compared using prediction interval overlap and normalized error metrics. All three model predictions fall within the 95% prediction interval of experimental results. Maximum normalized RMS error across teams is 8.3%, within the pre-specified acceptance threshold of 15%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and peak bending moment at yield are the quantities of interest directly relevant to regulatory submission requirements for spinal implant systems under ASTM F1717. QoI selection justified by clinical biomechanical rationale linking construct stiffness to fusion environment and implant fatigue life."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities replicate the exact ASTM F1717 test configuration that constitutes the regulatory submission test. The FEA ensemble models the same screw geometry, rod diameter, block material, and loading fixture as the physical test. Validation domain is therefore coincident with the submission test domain, providing high relevance."
    }
